[
  {
    "text": "♪ (Mellow instrumental hip-hop music) ♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=3"
  },
  {
    "text": "Praveen Sharma: Hi. My name is Praveen, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I'm from the Prototyping team here at Apple.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=11"
  },
  {
    "text": "Kai Kang: Hi. My name is Kai ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=14"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I'm from the Video Engineering team.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=15"
  },
  {
    "text": "Praveen: Over the past few years Apple has enabled ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=18"
  },
  {
    "text": "powerful new ways for people to bring the world into their apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=20"
  },
  {
    "text": "Last year, we introduced Object Capture, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "which takes in photos of real-world objects, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=28"
  },
  {
    "text": "and using the Photogrammetry API in RealityKit, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=31"
  },
  {
    "text": "turns them into a 3D model ready for use in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=34"
  },
  {
    "text": "Previous to Object Capture, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=39"
  },
  {
    "text": "we released the Scene Reconstruction API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=41"
  },
  {
    "text": "which gives you a coarse understanding ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=44"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the geometric structure of your space ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=46"
  },
  {
    "text": "and enables brand-new augmented reality use cases ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=52"
  },
  {
    "text": "This year, we are very excited to announce ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=54"
  },
  {
    "text": "a brand-new framework called RoomPlan.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=57"
  },
  {
    "text": "RoomPlan allows you to scan your room ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "using your LiDAR-enabled iPhone or iPad.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=64"
  },
  {
    "text": "It generates a parametric 3D model of the room ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=67"
  },
  {
    "text": "and its room-defining objects which you can use in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a look at what a RoomPlan scanning experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "looks like.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "RoomPlan uses sophisticated machine learning algorithms ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "powered by ARKit to detect walls, windows, openings, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=85"
  },
  {
    "text": "and doors, as well as room-defining objects ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=91"
  },
  {
    "text": "like fireplaces, couches, tables, and cabinets.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "With our RoomCaptureView API, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=100"
  },
  {
    "text": "which uses RealityKit to render scanning progress in real time, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=102"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can easily integrate a scanning experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=107"
  },
  {
    "text": "into your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "And when you are finished scanning, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "RoomCaptureView presents the final post-processed results ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=115"
  },
  {
    "text": "for you to use however best fits your use case.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "For the first time, without the complexities of implementing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=124"
  },
  {
    "text": "machine learning and computer vision algorithms, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "people can now interact with their room in brand new ways.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=130"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, interior design apps can preview ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "wall color changes and accurately calculate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=137"
  },
  {
    "text": "the amount of paint required to repaint a room.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "Architecture apps can now easily allow someone to preview ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=144"
  },
  {
    "text": "and edit changes to their room's layout in real time.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=147"
  },
  {
    "text": "Real estate apps can now seamlessly enable agents ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=151"
  },
  {
    "text": "to capture floor plans and 3D models of a listing.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "And e-commerce apps can engage customers ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=159"
  },
  {
    "text": "through product visualization in their physical spaces.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=161"
  },
  {
    "text": "These are just a few examples of applications RoomPlan enables, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=166"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you'll be surprised to see how simple it is ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "to integrate RoomPlan into your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=172"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a look.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=176"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are two main ways you can use RoomPlan.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=177"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first is our out-of-the-box scanning experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=181"
  },
  {
    "text": "which allows you to seamlessly integrate RoomPlan ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=184"
  },
  {
    "text": "into your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=186"
  },
  {
    "text": "The second is our data API which enables your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "to use the live parametric data from a scan ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=192"
  },
  {
    "text": "however best suits your use case.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=195"
  },
  {
    "text": "With both of these APIs, we recommend some best practices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=198"
  },
  {
    "text": "to help you achieve the best possible scan results, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=202"
  },
  {
    "text": "which we'll go over in the last section of this presentation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, let's talk about the scanning experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=210"
  },
  {
    "text": "that you can bring into your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=213"
  },
  {
    "text": "using our new RoomCaptureView API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=214"
  },
  {
    "text": "RoomCaptureView is a UIView subclass ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=218"
  },
  {
    "text": "that you can easily place in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=221"
  },
  {
    "text": "It handles the presentation of world space scanning feedback, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=223"
  },
  {
    "text": "real-time room model generation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=228"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as coaching and user guidance.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=230"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a closer look at the design elements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "presented during a RoomCaptureView-based scan.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "During an active RoomCaptureView session, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=241"
  },
  {
    "text": "animated lines outline detected walls, windows, openings, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=244"
  },
  {
    "text": "doors, and room-defining objects in real time.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=248"
  },
  {
    "text": "The interactive 3D model generated in real time ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "at the bottom of the RoomCaptureView, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=256"
  },
  {
    "text": "gives you an overview of your scanning progress at a glance.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, text coaching guides you ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=263"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the best possible scanning results.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=265"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a look at how you can start using RoomCaptureView ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=269"
  },
  {
    "text": "in just four easy steps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=272"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, we create a RoomCaptureView reference ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=275"
  },
  {
    "text": "in our ViewController.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=278"
  },
  {
    "text": "Second, we create a reference ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=280"
  },
  {
    "text": "to our RoomCaptureSession configuration object.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=283"
  },
  {
    "text": "Third, we start our scan session, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "passing in our configuration ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the capture session's run function.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=291"
  },
  {
    "text": "And finally, our application tells the capture session ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=294"
  },
  {
    "text": "to stop scanning.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=297"
  },
  {
    "text": "Optionally, your app can adhere to our RoomCaptureViewDelegate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=300"
  },
  {
    "text": "protocol and opt out of post-processed results ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=304"
  },
  {
    "text": "and their presentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=307"
  },
  {
    "text": "or handle the post-processed scan results ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=309"
  },
  {
    "text": "once they have been presented.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=311"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, you can export a USDZ of the results ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=314"
  },
  {
    "text": "by calling the export function available ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=318"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the provided CapturedRoom data struct.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=320"
  },
  {
    "text": "And that's how simple it is to integrate RoomPlan ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "into your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "We are so excited to see what you make with this API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now my colleague Kai will talk about RoomCaptureSession ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=332"
  },
  {
    "text": "and RoomPlan's Data API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=336"
  },
  {
    "text": "Kai: Thanks, Praveen.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=339"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this section, we will walk you through the Data APIs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "that provide you the access to the underlying data structures ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=343"
  },
  {
    "text": "during scanning and can help you build a custom visualization ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=346"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the scanning experience from ground up.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=351"
  },
  {
    "text": "The basic workflow consists of three parts: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=355"
  },
  {
    "text": "scan, process, and export.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=358"
  },
  {
    "text": "For scanning, we will cover the basics of how to set up ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=363"
  },
  {
    "text": "and start the capture session, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=366"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as display and monitor the capture process.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=368"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then we'll look at how your scanned data is processed ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=373"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the final model is received for presentation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=376"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, we'll discuss how you can generate and export ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=381"
  },
  {
    "text": "the output USD file which can also be used ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=385"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your USD workflows.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=389"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, let's look into the Scan step in detail.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=392"
  },
  {
    "text": "We will use the RoomCaptureSession API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=396"
  },
  {
    "text": "to set up the session and display the progress ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=399"
  },
  {
    "text": "as we continue scanning.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=401"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let me show you in code.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=403"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's a simple RealityKit app as an example.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=407"
  },
  {
    "text": "To start, simply import RoomPlan into your Swift project.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=410"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the ViewController of your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=416"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can have a custom type to visualize the results ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=418"
  },
  {
    "text": "and to initiate a RoomCaptureSession instance.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=421"
  },
  {
    "text": "Additionally, RoomCaptureSession provides a handle ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=425"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the underlying AR session so that your apps can draw planes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=429"
  },
  {
    "text": "and object bounding boxes in the AR view.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "RoomCaptureSession adopts the delegate pattern.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=437"
  },
  {
    "text": "In your ViewController class, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=440"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can assign the ViewController itself ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=441"
  },
  {
    "text": "as the captureSession's delegate.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=444"
  },
  {
    "text": "This would allow the ViewController ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=446"
  },
  {
    "text": "to get real-time updates from the RoomCaptureSession.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=448"
  },
  {
    "text": "Theses updates include 3D models and instructions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=453"
  },
  {
    "text": "in order to guide people during the capture.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=456"
  },
  {
    "text": "To get these updates, your ViewController ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=459"
  },
  {
    "text": "needs to conform to the RoomCaptureSessionDelegate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=462"
  },
  {
    "text": "protocol and implement two methods.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=465"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first one is ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=468"
  },
  {
    "text": "captureSession(_ session: didUpdate room:) method ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=470"
  },
  {
    "text": "in order to get the real-time CapturedRoom data structure.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=472"
  },
  {
    "text": "Your visualizer can use it to update AR view of the 3D model, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=477"
  },
  {
    "text": "which provides real-time feedback to people ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=481"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the progress.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=483"
  },
  {
    "text": "We will dive into the CapturedRoom structure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=485"
  },
  {
    "text": "more in a later part of the talk.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=488"
  },
  {
    "text": "This method will be called when we detect updates ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=491"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the captured room.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=493"
  },
  {
    "text": "The second method is ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=496"
  },
  {
    "text": "captureSession(_ session: didProvide instruction:).",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=497"
  },
  {
    "text": "This method provides you with an instruction structure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=501"
  },
  {
    "text": "which contains real-time feedback.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=504"
  },
  {
    "text": "Your visualizer can use the instruction ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=507"
  },
  {
    "text": "to guide people during the scan.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's go through the instructions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=513"
  },
  {
    "text": "that this API provides.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=514"
  },
  {
    "text": "These instructions include distance to the objects, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=517"
  },
  {
    "text": "scanning speed, lighting adjustment to the room, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=522"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as focusing on specific areas of the room ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=527"
  },
  {
    "text": "that have more textures.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=530"
  },
  {
    "text": "These instructions will be provided during the scan ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=533"
  },
  {
    "text": "in order to guide people with real-time feedback.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=536"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, we will move on to the process part.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=541"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this section, we will use the RoomBuilder class ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=544"
  },
  {
    "text": "to process the scanned data and generate the final 3D models.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=547"
  },
  {
    "text": "To process the captured data, the first step is to initiate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=553"
  },
  {
    "text": "a RoomBuilder instance in your ViewController class.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=557"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, in order to receive the sensor data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=561"
  },
  {
    "text": "after the capture process, your app needs to implement ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=564"
  },
  {
    "text": "the captureSession(_ session: didEndWith data: error:) method.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=567"
  },
  {
    "text": "When the RoomCaptureSession is stopped, by calling ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=572"
  },
  {
    "text": "the stop() function in your app, or due to an error, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=574"
  },
  {
    "text": "this function will be called to return a CaptureRoomData object ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=578"
  },
  {
    "text": "and an optional error.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=582"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, to process the captured data, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=585"
  },
  {
    "text": "we call the roomBuilder's async roomModel(from:) method ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=588"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the await keyword.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=592"
  },
  {
    "text": "The method runs asynchronously to process the scanned data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=595"
  },
  {
    "text": "and build the final 3D model.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=598"
  },
  {
    "text": "It utilizes the Swift async/await function ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=601"
  },
  {
    "text": "that we introduced in last year's WWDC.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=605"
  },
  {
    "text": "Within just a few seconds, the model will be available ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=609"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the final presentation in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=612"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, let's dive into the details ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=617"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the CapturedRoom data structure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=619"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how you can export it to use in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=621"
  },
  {
    "text": "At the top level, there is CapturedRoom ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=626"
  },
  {
    "text": "which consists of Surfaces and Objects.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=628"
  },
  {
    "text": "Surface contains unique attributes to represent curves ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=632"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as radius; starting and ending angles; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=636"
  },
  {
    "text": "four different edges of the surface; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=640"
  },
  {
    "text": "and architecture categories of wall, opening, window, door.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=643"
  },
  {
    "text": "Object contains furniture categories ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=649"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as table, bed, sofa, etc.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=652"
  },
  {
    "text": "Surface and Object share some common attributes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=656"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as dimensions; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=660"
  },
  {
    "text": "confidence, which gives you three levels of confidence ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=662"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the scanned surface or object; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=665"
  },
  {
    "text": "the 3D transform matrix; as well as a unique identifier.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=668"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's see how they are represented in code.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=673"
  },
  {
    "text": "The CapturedRoom structure is a fully parametric representation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=677"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the elements in the room.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=681"
  },
  {
    "text": "It contains five properties including walls, openings, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=683"
  },
  {
    "text": "doors, windows, and objects in the room.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=687"
  },
  {
    "text": "For the first four elements, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=691"
  },
  {
    "text": "they are represented as the Surface structure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=693"
  },
  {
    "text": "which represents 2D planar architectural structures.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=696"
  },
  {
    "text": "On the right, you can see the various properties ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=701"
  },
  {
    "text": "of Surface we covered earlier.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=703"
  },
  {
    "text": "The last property is an array of 3D objects in the room, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=707"
  },
  {
    "text": "and they are represented as cuboids.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=711"
  },
  {
    "text": "On the right, you can see the various properties of Object.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=714"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is the list of object types we support in RoomPlan.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=719"
  },
  {
    "text": "These include a variety of common furniture types ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=724"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as sofa, table, chair, bed, and many more.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=727"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, the export function allows you to export ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=732"
  },
  {
    "text": "this CapturedRoom into a USD or USDZ data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=736"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your existing workflows.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=740"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is an example to show how you can directly open ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=744"
  },
  {
    "text": "the USD output in Cinema 4D ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=747"
  },
  {
    "text": "to browse and edit the hierarchical data structure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=750"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the room, as well as the dimensions and location ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=753"
  },
  {
    "text": "of each room element or object.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=755"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can also leverage your existing USD and USDZ workflows ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=760"
  },
  {
    "text": "to add renders of the captured room ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=764"
  },
  {
    "text": "into a variety of applications such as real estate, e-commerce, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=767"
  },
  {
    "text": "utilities, and interior design.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=772"
  },
  {
    "text": "So far, we covered the scanning experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=777"
  },
  {
    "text": "and underlying RoomPlan APIs.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=779"
  },
  {
    "text": "We'll now go through some best practices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=782"
  },
  {
    "text": "to help you get good results with RoomPlan.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=784"
  },
  {
    "text": "We will cover the recommended conditions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=789"
  },
  {
    "text": "that allow for a good scan, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=790"
  },
  {
    "text": "room features to look out for while selecting a room, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=792"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as a few scanning and thermal considerations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=796"
  },
  {
    "text": "to keep in mind.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=799"
  },
  {
    "text": "RoomPlan API supports most common architectural structures ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=802"
  },
  {
    "text": "and objects in a typical household.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=806"
  },
  {
    "text": "It works best for a single residential room ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=809"
  },
  {
    "text": "with a maximum room size of 30 feet by 30 feet ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=811"
  },
  {
    "text": "or around 9 by 9 meters.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=815"
  },
  {
    "text": "Lighting is also important for the API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=818"
  },
  {
    "text": "to get a clear video stream and good AR tracking performance.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=820"
  },
  {
    "text": "A minimum 50 lux or higher is recommended for using the API, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=825"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is typical for a family living room at night.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=830"
  },
  {
    "text": "For the hardware, RoomPlan API is supported on all ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=834"
  },
  {
    "text": "LiDAR-enabled iPhone and iPad Pro models.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=837"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are some special conditions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=842"
  },
  {
    "text": "that can present a challenge for the API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=844"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, full-height mirrors and glass pose a challenge ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=847"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the LiDAR sensor to produce the expected output.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=851"
  },
  {
    "text": "Even high ceilings could exceed the limit of the scanning range ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=855"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the LiDAR sensor.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=858"
  },
  {
    "text": "Also, very dark surfaces could be hard for the device to scan.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=860"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are some considerations to get better scanning results.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=867"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, for applications that have high accuracy requirements, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=871"
  },
  {
    "text": "preparing the room before scanning ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=876"
  },
  {
    "text": "can enhance the quality of the scan.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=878"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, opening the curtains ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=881"
  },
  {
    "text": "can let more natural light in and reduce window occlusions, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=883"
  },
  {
    "text": "which works best for daytime scans.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=887"
  },
  {
    "text": "Closing the doors can reduce the chance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=890"
  },
  {
    "text": "of scanning unnecessary area outside of the room.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=893"
  },
  {
    "text": "Following a good scanning motion is also very important ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=897"
  },
  {
    "text": "to achieving good scanning results with the API.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=900"
  },
  {
    "text": "And that is why we provide the user instruction delegate method ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=903"
  },
  {
    "text": "in order to provide feedback on textures, distance, speed, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=907"
  },
  {
    "text": "and lighting conditions to people during the scans.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=912"
  },
  {
    "text": "Another thing to keep in mind ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=916"
  },
  {
    "text": "is battery and thermals of the device.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=918"
  },
  {
    "text": "We have done many optimizations on RoomPlan API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=921"
  },
  {
    "text": "to ensure a good scanning experience.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=924"
  },
  {
    "text": "Nevertheless, it's best to avoid repeated scans ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=927"
  },
  {
    "text": "or single long scans over 5 minutes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=930"
  },
  {
    "text": "These could not only cause fatigue ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=934"
  },
  {
    "text": "but also drain out the battery and create thermal issues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=936"
  },
  {
    "text": "which might in turn impact the user experience of your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=939"
  },
  {
    "text": "There is a lot that we covered today.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=945"
  },
  {
    "text": "We introduced a brand-new API, RoomPlan.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=947"
  },
  {
    "text": "It provides an intuitive scanning experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=950"
  },
  {
    "text": "to capture your rooms, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=952"
  },
  {
    "text": "powerful machine learning models to understand the environment, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10127/?time=954"
  },
  {
